<D>__{oh, helen found me something in a real estate office, but...}
<C>__{toby}
<D>__{so now you can go! oh. oh! i am so damn glad to get out of this place! i will be in 'fourth form.' doesn't that sound great? and if you get a two bedroom place in d.c., i can come for vacations and summers. i'm out. i'm out!}
<A>__{caroline's eyes well up, and she lights a cigarette.}
<C>__{toby}
<P>__{(notices she's upset)}
<D>__{what? oh, don't cry he's not worth it.}
<A>__{as sad as she is, caroline smiles...}
<B>__{toby}
<A>__{she holds toby at arm's length and studies him.}
<C>__{caroline}
<D>__{my you've grown, haven't you.}
<A>__{then clutches him to her fiercely. smiling, the two walk on through the sunny afternoon, singing softly to each other.}
